          "returnType": "Promise<SceneDirector>",
          "description": "Switch to a fresh instance of target, ending the previously active scene permanently — unless options.retainCurrent is set, in which case the outgoing scene is suspended and retained (keyed by its constructor) for a later SceneDirector.restoreScene call instead. Ordinary switching always creates a fresh instance (definition §11.4) — this differs from the old instance-based API's same-instance no-op check, which no longer applies. An optional fade transition runs the swap at full opacity. The new scene completes load()+init() before the old one is torn down, so there is no blank frame between them, and the outgoing scene keeps running until the switch boundary is crossed. Rejects with ConcurrentSceneNavigationError when another navigation is already in flight (dev and production builds — no queueing, definition §11.5); with UnregisteredSceneError (dev builds) when target is not present in ApplicationOptions.scenes; with RetainedSceneConflictError when target already has a retained instance (restore or release it first)."
        },
